channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Israel's Military Warns 100,000 Residents in Gaza's Southern City of Rafah to Evacuate Immediately
Speaker Johnson to discuss issues with Marjorie Taylor Green ahead of her threats to oust him
item.description: Speaker Mike Johnson is expected to meet privately, one-on-one, with Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene on Monday amid speculation that she may trigger her motion to vacate.

item.title: Biden Speaks With Netanyahu, Who Vowed 'We Will Stand Alone'
item.description: President Joe Biden and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu spoke Monday morning, a White House official and a National Security Council spokesperson said.

item.title: Donald Trump Faces Possible Jail Time for Gag Order Violation in Manhattan Case
Ex-top Biden DOJ official now prosecuting Trump was once paid by DNC for 'political consulting'
item.description: EXCLUSIVE: The Democratic National Committee paid prosecutor Matthew Colangelo thousands of dollars for “political consulting" in 2018, Fox News Digital has learned.

item.title: Pollster to Newsmax: Biden 'Weak, Corrupt' and 'Polls Show it'
item.description: Six months before the U.S. presidential election, former President Donald Trump continues to lead President Joe Biden, pollsters John McLaughlin and John Zogby told Newsmax on Monday.

item.title: Illinois Just Rigged Its 2024 Election, and the 'Democracy' Defenders Are Nowhere to Be Found
NY v Trump: Judge threatens jail time for 'possibly the next president' for future gag order violations
item.description: Judge Juan Merchan on Monday said he will consider a jail sentence for former President Trump if he continues to violate the gag order imposed upon him in his unprecedented criminal trial.

item.title: Rep. Greene Could Trigger Motion to Vacate on Monday
item.description: Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene, R-Ga., could trigger her motion to vacate the House speakership on Monday, a source told Newsmax Senior Congressional Correspondent Kilmeny Duchardt.

item.title: Man Points Gun at Pastor Delivering Sermon, Some Call What Happened Next a 'Miracle'
Noem addresses feeling 'threatened' by Nikki Haley, a controversial dog killing, Trump VP speculation in book
item.description: Gov. Kristi Noem's new book, titled "No Going Back," details her life in politics and several controversial topics discussed in an interview with Fox News Digital.

item.title: Trump: Rep. Cuellar 'Respected Democrat Congressman'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump harshly criticized President Joe Biden on Monday for the indictment of Rep. Henry Cuellar, D-Texas, claiming on Truth Social that charges were brought against Cuellar only because he opposed Biden's policies on the southern border.

item.title: VP Harris Arrives in Michigan for a Campaign Stop With a UAW Job-Killing Package
House Dems seeking re-election seemingly reverse course, call on Biden to 'bring order to the southern border'
item.description: Five House Democrats who voted against measures to strengthen border security in the past have seemingly changed their tune as they seek re-election.

item.title: Trump Hit With 10th Gag Order Violation, Judge Weighs Jail Time
item.description: New York Judge Juan Merchan on Monday found Donald Trump guilty of a 10th gag order violation and fined the forner president an additional $1,000.
